  "title": "feat: use shared highlight component in vue3",
  "body": "**Summary**\r\n\r\n[FX-2748](https://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/FX-2748)\r\n\r\n**Result**\r\n\r\nAll existing tests pass for both vue2 and vue3.\r\n\r\nHad to get rid of the Vue3 example I made because of CodeSandbox running Node 16, but we can make one later when CodeSandbox's version is updated.\r\n\r\nAs components are different for Vue2 and Vue3, I organized the code so that once we remove support for Vue2 we won't have any changes to do to the Highlighter component, which is why it doesn't import from `vue-compat`.\r\n\r\n[FX-2748]: https://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/FX-2748?atlOrigin=eyJpIjoiNWRkNTljNzYxNjVmNDY3MDlhMDU5Y2ZhYzA5YTRkZjUiLCJwIjoiZ2l0aHViLWNvbS1KU1cifQ",
